WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Alhamdu Lillahi Rabbil Alameen

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Ar-Rahman Ar-Rahim

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Maliki Yawm Al-Din

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
Iyyaka Na'budu Wa Iyyaka Nastayim

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Ihdina Sirata Al-Mustaqeem

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
Sirata Al-Laleen An'ant Alayhim

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Ghayri Al-Mawdob Alayhim

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:35.680
Assalamu Alaikum Warahmatullahi Wabarakatuh

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:39.680
Bismillah Ar-Rahman Ar-Rahim Al-Hamdu Lillahi Rabbil Alameen

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:42.680
Wabiyya Nastayim Wa Nusalli Wa Nusallim

00:00:42.680 --> 00:00:45.680
Ala Afzal Al-Khalqi Ajmaeen Nabi'ina Muhammad

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:48.680
Wa Ala Alihi Wa Sahbihi Wa At-Tabi'ina Wa Man Tabi'ahum

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:51.680
Bi Ihsanin Ila Yawm Al-Din Wa Ba'd

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:57.680
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and send blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:00:57.680 --> 00:01:02.680
His entire household may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless all of them as well as his companions

00:01:02.680 --> 00:01:05.680
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless every single one of us

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:06.680
Ameen

00:01:06.680 --> 00:01:08.680
Beloved brothers and sisters

00:01:08.680 --> 00:01:12.680
We had seen how after the treaty of Hudaybiyah

00:01:12.680 --> 00:01:14.680
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:21.680
Decided to send letters to the various leaders and kings in the region and even outside the region

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:26.680
This was the first time that ambassadors were sent in this particular way

00:01:26.680 --> 00:01:29.680
Where a letter was written

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:32.680
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam being unlettered

00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:36.680
He instructed people from his companions who could write

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:37.680
To write the letters

00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:39.680
They were short to the point

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:41.680
The message was delivered

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:45.680
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam sent his ambassadors across

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:50.680
We heard about Dihya Ibn Khalifah Al-Kalbi r.a

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:54.680
Who was sent to Heraclius of the Roman Empire

00:01:54.680 --> 00:01:58.680
Who was based in a sham because that was under the Roman Empire

00:01:58.680 --> 00:02:00.680
He was not the king of the Romans

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:06.680
But he was the emperor at the time of that particular area that fell under the Roman Empire

00:02:06.680 --> 00:02:11.680
So we also heard of how he reacted and how he asked several questions

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:13.680
And the fact that he knew what was right and wrong

00:02:13.680 --> 00:02:16.680
But because he wanted to stick to his throne

00:02:16.680 --> 00:02:20.680
And he did not want to earn the wrath of his own men

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:23.680
And that is why he did not accept the message

00:02:23.680 --> 00:02:27.680
But he sent back Dihya Ibn Khalifah Al-Kalbi with much respect

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:31.680
A point that we learn from this particular incident is

00:02:31.680 --> 00:02:37.680
When the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam wrote a letter to this Heraclius

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.680
His companions told him this man is not going to read your letter

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:46.680
Because in order to officialize letters which go to the Romans

00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:49.680
You need to have a stamp on the letter

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:55.680
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam then asked some of his companions what should be done

00:02:55.680 --> 00:03:03.680
And they suggested to him that he get a ring that was made of silver with his name on it

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.680
Muhammadun Rasulullah

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:10.680
And what would happen is normally it would be written starting from the bottom going up

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:13.680
So Muhammadun Rasulullah

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:15.680
And therefore he had a ring

00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:17.680
This was not part of jewelry

00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:21.680
But it was part of the stamping

00:03:21.680 --> 00:03:25.680
That the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had decided to do

00:03:25.680 --> 00:03:29.680
Because of the letters that had to be sent to these Romans

00:03:29.680 --> 00:03:32.680
And the fact that they would not be read unless they had a stamp

00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:34.680
We learn a lot from this

00:03:34.680 --> 00:03:37.680
This was something that was not the way of the Muslims

00:03:37.680 --> 00:03:41.680
But it became the way of the Muslims when the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam did it

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.680
He heard that they were doing it

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:48.680
And therefore in order to give the message across or to get the message across

00:03:48.680 --> 00:03:52.680
He decided to do something that was new to Islam and the Muslims

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:56.680
And from this very interesting point that I just want to add in here

00:03:56.680 --> 00:04:00.680
Some of the people say it is Sunnah to wear a silver ring

00:04:00.680 --> 00:04:04.680
And some of the scholars say no, it is a Sunnah to wear a ring

00:04:04.680 --> 00:04:08.680
If you cannot read and write and you have your name inscribed on it

00:04:08.680 --> 00:04:10.680
And you would like to stamp letters

00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:12.680
So it's just a little difference of opinion

00:04:13.680 --> 00:04:17.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us and grant us the acceptance

00:04:17.680 --> 00:04:20.680
To follow the Sunnah of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:24.680
Many times we find we just follow that which is convenient for us

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.680
And when it comes to those things that are a little bit more difficult

00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:29.680
We tend to ignore them completely

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:31.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors

00:04:31.680 --> 00:04:35.680
So the hadith of this ring is mentioned in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:37.680
Reported by Anas ibn Malik radiallahu anhu

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:41.680
And he says I could actually see the white mark on the finger of Rasulullah

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:43.680
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam from the ring

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:48.680
The other letter that was sent was sent to Kisra

00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:51.680
The Persians what we know today as Iran

00:04:51.680 --> 00:04:53.680
That is where Kisra was based

00:04:53.680 --> 00:04:59.680
And the man sent to him was Abdullah ibn Hudhafah al-Sahmi radiallahu anhu

00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:02.680
Whether he got exactly to Kisra right there

00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:05.680
Or whether the letter was then taken by one of Kisra's men

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:06.680
There are two narrations

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:10.680
But when Kisra got the letter of the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:13.680
He became so angry, so upset

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:14.680
Who is this man?

00:05:14.680 --> 00:05:17.680
He ripped the letter of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:05:17.680 --> 00:05:19.680
Threw it on the floor and stamped on it

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:21.680
What a great disrespect

00:05:21.680 --> 00:05:24.680
When the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam heard of this reaction

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:25.680
He said

00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:29.680
May Allah rip his kingdom as well

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:31.680
In the same way he has ripped our letter

00:05:31.680 --> 00:05:33.680
There was no need to rip the letter

00:05:33.680 --> 00:05:37.680
So it is reported that within a very short space of time

00:05:37.680 --> 00:05:40.680
There was civil war in Persia

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:44.680
And his own son murdered him and took over

00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:49.680
And there was chaos which resulted in the end of that particular empire

00:05:49.680 --> 00:05:51.680
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us strength

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:53.680
And may He grant us a lesson

00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:59.680
We do not disrespect that which is sacred in the eyes of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:05:59.680 --> 00:06:01.680
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam open our doors

00:06:01.680 --> 00:06:03.680
Then there was An-Najashi

00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:07.680
We know the Negus who was based in Abyssinia

00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:12.680
The Muslims but with the leadership of Ja'far ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:17.680
Were sent for the first migration to Abyssinia

00:06:17.680 --> 00:06:18.680
They were still there

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:21.680
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam wrote another letter to him

00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:24.680
Several letters were actually written to this Najashi

00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:26.680
His name was Ashamah

00:06:26.680 --> 00:06:30.680
And the Negus was just the title given to the leader of Abyssinia

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:34.680
Where we would say Ethiopia, Eritrea that is today

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:38.680
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us all a lesson from what had happened

00:06:38.680 --> 00:06:46.680
When the letter came, it came with Amr ibn Abi Umayyah al-Zamri radiallahu anhu

00:06:46.680 --> 00:06:48.680
And he presented it to An-Najashi

00:06:48.680 --> 00:06:50.680
An-Najashi read it

00:06:50.680 --> 00:06:53.680
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam always wrote

00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:59.680
Connecting the writing to the beliefs of the particular person he was writing to

00:06:59.680 --> 00:07:04.680
So when he wrote to An-Najashi, he made a few clarifications about Jesus may peace be upon him

00:07:04.680 --> 00:07:08.680
This is who he was and this is what we believe he is and so on

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:10.680
So An-Najashi read the letter

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:14.680
He thereafter said, look, I know that this is all correct

00:07:14.680 --> 00:07:16.680
I actually believe it

00:07:16.680 --> 00:07:21.680
But I would like you to know that I don't have much support amongst my top brass

00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:24.680
And therefore give me a little bit of time

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:26.680
And I will then gain that support

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:31.680
And thereafter, I will announce that we have accepted this faith and so on

00:07:31.680 --> 00:07:38.680
So these are the narrations that make mention of the Negus of Abyssinia and what his response was

00:07:38.680 --> 00:07:45.680
And thereafter, it is also made mention of another letter that was written to An-Najashi

00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:48.680
Which I will pause for a moment and make mention of right now

00:07:48.680 --> 00:07:52.680
There was a Sahabiyya known as Ramla binti Abi Sufyan

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:55.680
The daughter of Abu Sufyan himself

00:07:55.680 --> 00:07:58.680
Her name was Ramla binti Abi Sufyan

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:02.680
She was married to a man known as Ubaidillahi ibn Jahsh

00:08:02.680 --> 00:08:04.680
The brother of Abdullah ibn Jahsh

00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:10.680
This Ubaidillahi ibn Jahsh with his wife Ramla binti Abi Sufyan

00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:15.680
They were from amongst the believers who believed early and they had migrated to Abyssinia

00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:17.680
This man passed away

00:08:17.680 --> 00:08:20.680
Exactly how he passed away, there are different narrations

00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:23.680
Some say he had developed bad habits and so on

00:08:23.680 --> 00:08:25.680
And he passed away

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:30.680
And this daughter of Abu Sufyan, she was now known as Ummu Habibah

00:08:30.680 --> 00:08:34.680
Because she had had a child known as Habibah from Ubaidillahi ibn Jahsh

00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:39.680
So because she was the daughter of the leader and now she is without a husband

00:08:39.680 --> 00:08:43.680
What should she do? She was an elderly lady, she wasn't a young girl

00:08:43.680 --> 00:08:45.680
And she had made Hijra

00:08:45.680 --> 00:08:49.680
She was from amongst the first believers which means if we were to make them

00:08:49.680 --> 00:08:55.680
Or if we were to consider those who had accepted Islam before the migration to Abyssinia

00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:58.680
As the first believers, she was from amongst them

00:08:58.680 --> 00:09:03.680
And so if she returned to Mecca, she was going to be persecuted

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:06.680
Being what a disgrace to Abu Sufyan being a leader

00:09:06.680 --> 00:09:09.680
And his daughter is following Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:09:09.680 --> 00:09:13.680
And if she was to go elsewhere, what would happen to her?

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:17.680
So the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam wrote a letter to An-Najashi

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.680
Sent it with one of his companions

00:09:20.680 --> 00:09:26.680
And told him that when this woman has completed her iddah, a certain period of time

00:09:26.680 --> 00:09:29.680
Then I would like to marry her

00:09:29.680 --> 00:09:32.680
So she was married to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:09:32.680 --> 00:09:35.680
While she was still in Abyssinia

00:09:35.680 --> 00:09:41.680
Under the eye of this An-Najashi that the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam had sent

00:09:41.680 --> 00:09:47.680
And her guardian was a man known as Khalid ibn Saeed ibn al-Aas radiallahu anhu

00:09:47.680 --> 00:09:52.680
Ummu Habibah radiallahu anhu became known as Ummu al-Mumineen

00:09:52.680 --> 00:09:56.680
She became known as the mother of the believers Ramla binti Abi Sufyan

00:09:56.680 --> 00:10:03.680
And by this action, the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam became very closely related to Abu Sufyan radiallahu anhu

00:10:03.680 --> 00:10:06.680
So much so that he was married to his own daughter

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:09.680
So this had happened in Abyssinia

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:15.680
And later on, the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam had instructed the man who had carried the letter

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:19.680
Who was Amr ibn Umayyah al-Dumri or al-Dumri radiallahu anhu

00:10:19.680 --> 00:10:25.680
To find out about those who had migrated and informed them that we are sitting in a period of grace

00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:28.680
And you may now return to Al-Madinatul Munawwara

00:10:28.680 --> 00:10:30.680
They began to plan and to prepare

00:10:30.680 --> 00:10:33.680
And they later started their journey inshallah

00:10:33.680 --> 00:10:36.680
We will get to when they arrived in Madinatul Munawwara

00:10:36.680 --> 00:10:40.680
Just as the victory of Khaybar was announced

00:10:40.680 --> 00:10:47.680
This is when Ja'far ibn Abi Talib and the others had arrived in Madinatul Munawwara together with Ummu Habibah radiallahu anhu

00:10:47.680 --> 00:10:50.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala be pleased with her

00:10:50.680 --> 00:10:53.680
So if you look at Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam's marriages

00:10:53.680 --> 00:10:58.680
They were always out of the mercy that Allah had placed in his heart

00:10:58.680 --> 00:11:02.680
For those who had sacrificed for the purpose of the deen

00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:06.680
He had gone forth in order to save them from difficulty

00:11:06.680 --> 00:11:09.680
To give them the guardianship that they needed

00:11:09.680 --> 00:11:12.680
And in order to be a pillar of support and strength for them

00:11:12.680 --> 00:11:15.680
And this had happened in most of the cases as you know

00:11:15.680 --> 00:11:17.680
He only married one virgin

00:11:17.680 --> 00:11:19.680
The rest of them were non-virgins

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:22.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a lesson from this

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:26.680
Where are those who want to point fingers at Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:26.680 --> 00:11:31.680
They cannot even be kind to their own wives and they want to speak

00:11:31.680 --> 00:11:33.680
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:33.680 --> 00:11:35.680
Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:39.680
He had such a great concern that he used to encourage his companions

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:42.680
To look after the widows, the divorce, the orphans

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:46.680
Those who have sacrificed for the pleasure of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:50.680
Thereafter another letter was sent to a man known as Muqawqis

00:11:50.680 --> 00:11:53.680
Al Muqawqis, he was the leader of Egypt at the time

00:11:53.680 --> 00:11:56.680
And it is reported that Hatib ibn Abi Balta'ah

00:11:56.680 --> 00:11:58.680
According to some historians

00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:01.680
Was sent to Al Muqawqis with the letter

00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:04.680
This man got the letter, he did not accept Islam

00:12:04.680 --> 00:12:07.680
He understood very well what the letter said

00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:10.680
And he decided look let me send some gifts with this man

00:12:10.680 --> 00:12:12.680
Hatib ibn Abi Balta'ah

00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:14.680
Radhiallahu antu Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:12:14.680 --> 00:12:16.680
And he makes mention of something important

00:12:16.680 --> 00:12:18.680
He wrote back a letter

00:12:18.680 --> 00:12:22.680
And he says look I have understood what you said and what you know

00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:26.680
So on and I am sending you a few gifts from amongst them

00:12:26.680 --> 00:12:28.680
Are two ladies

00:12:28.680 --> 00:12:32.680
Now the term Jariya does not necessarily refer to slave girls

00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:35.680
No, it also refers to young girls

00:12:35.680 --> 00:12:38.680
And it refers to young ladies as well

00:12:38.680 --> 00:12:41.680
You could say a Jariya referring to a young girl

00:12:41.680 --> 00:12:46.680
So he says I am sending you two of these girls

00:12:46.680 --> 00:12:50.680
Who are from the highest lineages of the Qibla

00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:53.680
The Aqbaat are the Coptic Christians of Egypt

00:12:53.680 --> 00:12:55.680
And remember Christianity and Islam

00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:56.680
As well as Judaism

00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:00.680
They come from the same lantern as what Najashi had said

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:03.680
From the same lantern meaning the pure form of Judaism

00:13:03.680 --> 00:13:05.680
And the pure form of Christianity

00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:08.680
Would lead you to the pure form of Islam

00:13:08.680 --> 00:13:11.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:13.680
And then when he had sent

00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:17.680
He sent an animal as well a mule according to some narrations

00:13:17.680 --> 00:13:19.680
To Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:19.680 --> 00:13:20.680
With a few other gifts

00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:22.680
And the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:22.680 --> 00:13:24.680
Then took Maria al-Qibtiya

00:13:24.680 --> 00:13:27.680
And according to some narrations married her

00:13:27.680 --> 00:13:30.680
And according to some narrations he remained with her

00:13:30.680 --> 00:13:35.680
As a person who was gifted to him sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:37.680
I would incline more to the narration

00:13:37.680 --> 00:13:40.680
That states that he married her sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:40.680 --> 00:13:43.680
He had a child from her known as Ibrahim

00:13:43.680 --> 00:13:45.680
Ibn Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:47.680
Who passed away in his infancy

00:13:47.680 --> 00:13:50.680
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us goodness

00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:54.680
Many of us sometimes look at those who have lost children in their infancy

00:13:54.680 --> 00:13:59.680
And we lose track of the words we want to say to them

00:13:59.680 --> 00:14:02.680
One of the most powerful words we could utter to them

00:14:02.680 --> 00:14:06.680
After the dua and the reminder that everything is in the hands of Allah

00:14:06.680 --> 00:14:10.680
Is to remind them of what happened to the most blessed and best of creation

00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:12.680
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:14:12.680 --> 00:14:15.680
He lost most of his children before he passed away

00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:19.680
And he lost more than one wife before he passed away

00:14:19.680 --> 00:14:20.680
Subhanallah

00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:23.680
So he had lost many of his relatives

00:14:23.680 --> 00:14:25.680
In fact he was born an orphan

00:14:25.680 --> 00:14:28.680
And he lost his mother when he was also quite young

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:31.680
Thereafter we find a letter that was written

00:14:31.680 --> 00:14:34.680
To Al-Mundir Ibn Sawah al-Abdi of Bahrain

00:14:34.680 --> 00:14:35.680
The king of Bahrain

00:14:35.680 --> 00:14:39.680
This man Abu Al-Ala al-Hadhrami was sent to him

00:14:39.680 --> 00:14:40.680
Radhiallahu an

00:14:40.680 --> 00:14:42.680
And when he got the letter he understood it

00:14:42.680 --> 00:14:48.680
He accepted Islam and all the Arabs of Bahrain accepted Islam as well

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:49.680
They accepted Islam with him

00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:53.680
And the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam received a response from him

00:14:53.680 --> 00:14:58.680
And one of the methods of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam was that

00:14:58.680 --> 00:15:02.680
He did not remove those people from the leadership that they were holding

00:15:02.680 --> 00:15:06.680
But rather he helped them, he guided them and they remained the leaders

00:15:06.680 --> 00:15:08.680
So he remained the leader of Bahrain

00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:11.680
And he was instructed what to do with the others and so on

00:15:11.680 --> 00:15:15.680
And he was given instructions by Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:17.680
Which he followed properly

00:15:17.680 --> 00:15:22.680
Thereafter there was a letter also that was sent to one of the leaders of Yemen

00:15:22.680 --> 00:15:25.680
One of the Umara, one of the leaders of Yemen

00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:29.680
Who was known according to some of the historians as Badhan Ibn Sassan

00:15:29.680 --> 00:15:32.680
And this man had accepted Islam, the same thing happened

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:35.680
The Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam kept him there in Yemen

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:37.680
And even after he had passed away

00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:39.680
His son was allowed to take over from him

00:15:39.680 --> 00:15:44.680
And then there was a letter that was sent to the Amir of Busra

00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:48.680
That was also going up north to the region of Ash-Sham

00:15:48.680 --> 00:15:50.680
Where the Romans had been ruling

00:15:50.680 --> 00:15:54.680
And the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam sent a companion known as

00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:58.680
Al-Harith Ibn Umayr Al-Azdi radiallahu anhu

00:15:58.680 --> 00:16:02.680
On the way to Busra, he passed Muqta

00:16:02.680 --> 00:16:05.680
And in Muqta, Muqta is the name of an area

00:16:05.680 --> 00:16:08.680
The Ghassanites, the people from the clan of Ghassan

00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:10.680
They were ruling there

00:16:10.680 --> 00:16:13.680
And one of the men Shara Habib Ibn Amr Al-Ghassani

00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:17.680
He got hold of this ambassador of the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:16:17.680 --> 00:16:20.680
Where are you going? He says I'm going to the Amir of Busra

00:16:20.680 --> 00:16:23.680
So he tied him up and executed him

00:16:23.680 --> 00:16:25.680
So this was a messenger who was killed

00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:28.680
Later on the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:16:28.680 --> 00:16:32.680
Prepared an army of 3000 men that marched on to Muqta

00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:34.680
And inshallah we will get to that

00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:36.680
By the will of Allah perhaps tomorrow

00:16:36.680 --> 00:16:38.680
We will look into that particular war

00:16:38.680 --> 00:16:40.680
The reason of that war with those Romans

00:16:40.680 --> 00:16:43.680
Was because they had executed a man

00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:47.680
Who was an ambassador from Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:16:47.680 --> 00:16:48.680
To them

00:16:48.680 --> 00:16:51.680
So people must not think that the Muslims went out

00:16:51.680 --> 00:16:53.680
In order to spread their religion by the sword

00:16:53.680 --> 00:16:55.680
Never did that happen, subhanallah

00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:58.680
It was those who had attacked the Muslims

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:00.680
Those who had harmed them

00:17:00.680 --> 00:17:03.680
Revenge was permitted, retaliation was permitted

00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:06.680
And therefore, when they were attacked, they had attacked back

00:17:06.680 --> 00:17:09.680
Here there was a man, one man was executed

00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:11.680
What do you want the Muslims to do?

00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:13.680
Sit back and wait for the rest of them to be attacked

00:17:13.680 --> 00:17:15.680
Or prepare and go and tackle them

00:17:15.680 --> 00:17:17.680
Why did you do this to our man?

00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:21.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding

00:17:21.680 --> 00:17:25.680
Thereafter there were letters also that were sent

00:17:25.680 --> 00:17:28.680
Later on in the eighth year of Hijra

00:17:28.680 --> 00:17:30.680
Remember these letters were not all sent together

00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:32.680
I'm just clustering them together

00:17:32.680 --> 00:17:34.680
But they were spaced out

00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:36.680
Some of them were sent right at the beginning

00:17:36.680 --> 00:17:38.680
Whilst others were sent even later on

00:17:38.680 --> 00:17:41.680
Amr ibn al-Aas was not yet a Muslim

00:17:41.680 --> 00:17:43.680
But after he accepted Islam

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:47.680
The Prophet ﷺ sent him as well to Oman

00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:49.680
And there were two leaders there in Oman

00:17:49.680 --> 00:17:53.680
It is reported the names were Jafar and Abd

00:17:53.680 --> 00:17:55.680
They were known as Al-Jalandi

00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:58.680
And these people, they accepted Islam as well

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:01.680
Amr ibn al-Aas, who had accepted Islam

00:18:01.680 --> 00:18:04.680
By the time he had taken the letters and gone

00:18:04.680 --> 00:18:08.680
He had then brought news to the Prophet ﷺ

00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:12.680
Of the acceptance of Islam of these particular leaders

00:18:12.680 --> 00:18:14.680
So these were just some of the letters

00:18:14.680 --> 00:18:18.680
That were sent by Rasulullah ﷺ

00:18:18.680 --> 00:18:20.680
As you notice what happened is

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:22.680
Islam spread

00:18:22.680 --> 00:18:26.680
It spread further than Quraysh would ever have dreamt of

00:18:26.680 --> 00:18:29.680
And this is why amazingly

00:18:29.680 --> 00:18:32.680
Not only was Abu Sufyan from amongst those

00:18:32.680 --> 00:18:34.680
Who heard with his own ears

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.680
What Heraclius had to say

00:18:36.680 --> 00:18:40.680
But the others actually accepted Islam

00:18:40.680 --> 00:18:43.680
And not only tribes, nations accepted Islam

00:18:43.680 --> 00:18:46.680
Just by listening and by understanding this message is good

00:18:46.680 --> 00:18:48.680
I haven't gone into the details

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:50.680
But there are very interesting details

00:18:50.680 --> 00:18:53.680
Mentioned in the books of Seerah and the books of history

00:18:53.680 --> 00:18:56.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a lesson

00:18:56.680 --> 00:19:00.680
Now in the seventh year of Hijra, in Muharram

00:19:00.680 --> 00:19:03.680
The Prophet ﷺ

00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:06.680
Had had obviously a treaty with the people of Quraysh

00:19:06.680 --> 00:19:08.680
So he was not fighting the people of Quraysh

00:19:08.680 --> 00:19:13.680
Nor was he fighting those who were allied to the people of Quraysh

00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:15.680
There was an agreement we won't fight

00:19:15.680 --> 00:19:17.680
Ten years, peace

00:19:17.680 --> 00:19:21.680
But what about those Jewish tribes in Khaybar

00:19:21.680 --> 00:19:24.680
That had made the alliance

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:28.680
Or they were responsible for forming the alliance

00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:31.680
Of the confederates that had come to fight

00:19:31.680 --> 00:19:33.680
Resulting in the Battle of the Trench

00:19:33.680 --> 00:19:36.680
The Prophet ﷺ did not forget that

00:19:36.680 --> 00:19:39.680
He now told his people get ready we are going to Khaybar

00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:41.680
Because these people from Banu al-Nadir

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:44.680
Remember there was a man known as Huyay ibn Akhtab

00:19:44.680 --> 00:19:46.680
He was one of the leaders of Banu al-Nadir

00:19:46.680 --> 00:19:48.680
He had also run away to Khaybar

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:52.680
But somehow he was in Banu Qurayzah

00:19:52.680 --> 00:19:55.680
The time when Banu Qurayzah were being executed

00:19:55.680 --> 00:19:57.680
And he was one of them who was also executed

00:19:57.680 --> 00:20:00.680
At the time according to the books of Seerah

00:20:00.680 --> 00:20:03.680
But however his people and some others were there

00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:05.680
Including a daughter of his known as

00:20:05.680 --> 00:20:08.680
Safiyyah binti Huyay

00:20:08.680 --> 00:20:10.680
Later on to be known as Radiyallahu anha

00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:13.680
She accepted Islam just after Khaybar

00:20:13.680 --> 00:20:16.680
So the Prophet ﷺ prepared an army

00:20:16.680 --> 00:20:18.680
And they went up to Khaybar

00:20:18.680 --> 00:20:21.680
This they had fought these people of the book

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:24.680
And these people were sophisticated people

00:20:24.680 --> 00:20:28.680
They had built their homes in a very sophisticated way

00:20:28.680 --> 00:20:32.680
They had had three clusters of fortresses

00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:35.680
The first cluster had three forts

00:20:35.680 --> 00:20:37.680
The second cluster had two forts

00:20:37.680 --> 00:20:39.680
And the third cluster had three forts

00:20:39.680 --> 00:20:42.680
And they were built interleading in such a way

00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:45.680
That you could actually disappear from one to the other

00:20:45.680 --> 00:20:47.680
They were underground tunnels also

00:20:47.680 --> 00:20:49.680
Interleading some of these forts

00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:51.680
They were complicated people

00:20:51.680 --> 00:20:54.680
They mastered the art of fighting, subhanallah

00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:56.680
And they were well prepared for the Muslims

00:20:56.680 --> 00:21:00.680
Because they knew, we are the ones who have assisted

00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:03.680
And have had masterminded the whole alliance

00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:06.680
And today we are sitting, those two have made peace

00:21:06.680 --> 00:21:07.680
We are in trouble

00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:08.680
So they knew this was coming

00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:11.680
The Prophet ﷺ went to them, subhanallah

00:21:11.680 --> 00:21:15.680
And the first thing he got to one of

00:21:15.680 --> 00:21:17.680
I'm not going to take the names of every single fort

00:21:17.680 --> 00:21:18.680
There are plenty forts

00:21:18.680 --> 00:21:20.680
But he got to the first one

00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:24.680
And as he got there, they wanted to fight him

00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:25.680
The Prophet ﷺ thought

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:28.680
Let us cut down some of their trees

00:21:28.680 --> 00:21:30.680
In order for them to see the numbers

00:21:30.680 --> 00:21:31.680
That we have come in

00:21:31.680 --> 00:21:33.680
And we are here seriously

00:21:33.680 --> 00:21:36.680
We are here in order to retaliate

00:21:36.680 --> 00:21:39.680
Their masterminding of the army

00:21:39.680 --> 00:21:42.680
That came to wipe us out, subhanallah

00:21:42.680 --> 00:21:45.680
And by the help of Allah, the Muslims had won

00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:46.680
They were victorious

00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.680
Remember the wind came

00:21:48.680 --> 00:21:51.680
And the angels came and so on

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:53.680
So after they had cut it down

00:21:53.680 --> 00:21:55.680
These people, they still wanted to fight

00:21:55.680 --> 00:21:57.680
The Muslims overcame them

00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.680
And they had run through to the next fort

00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:02.680
See, subhanallah, very intelligent people

00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:04.680
Then when it came to the second fort

00:22:04.680 --> 00:22:05.680
What had happened?

00:22:05.680 --> 00:22:09.680
The Prophet ﷺ surrounded them

00:22:09.680 --> 00:22:12.680
And there was fighting that happened there again

00:22:12.680 --> 00:22:14.680
There was an attack that took place

00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:16.680
And after some time, it was quite difficult

00:22:16.680 --> 00:22:17.680
These people were attacking

00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:18.680
How were they attacking?

00:22:18.680 --> 00:22:20.680
With arrows, with spears

00:22:20.680 --> 00:22:23.680
And then Umar ibn Al-Khattab r.a succeeded

00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:25.680
To get hold of one of the men

00:22:25.680 --> 00:22:27.680
Who was trying to run away in the night

00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:28.680
And when he caught him

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:30.680
He brought him to Rasulullah ﷺ

00:22:30.680 --> 00:22:33.680
He says, oh messenger, I caught this man

00:22:33.680 --> 00:22:34.680
So he says, look, don't harm me

00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:35.680
If you don't harm me

00:22:35.680 --> 00:22:37.680
I will give you information

00:22:37.680 --> 00:22:39.680
Of how to overcome these people

00:22:39.680 --> 00:22:41.680
So the Prophet ﷺ said

00:22:41.680 --> 00:22:43.680
What is the news that you have?

00:22:43.680 --> 00:22:45.680
He says, these people are preparing

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:48.680
To attack you tomorrow with their army

00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:50.680
Meaning they are going to come weaponry

00:22:50.680 --> 00:22:51.680
They want to attack you

00:22:51.680 --> 00:22:53.680
If you overcome them

00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:55.680
I will lead you to a house

00:22:55.680 --> 00:22:58.680
Where there are so many catapults

00:22:58.680 --> 00:23:00.680
Now they had huge catapults

00:23:00.680 --> 00:23:02.680
What is known in the Arabic language

00:23:02.680 --> 00:23:04.680
As a manjaniq, more like a cannon

00:23:04.680 --> 00:23:07.680
Where they would put a ball of fire

00:23:07.680 --> 00:23:08.680
On one end of it

00:23:08.680 --> 00:23:11.680
And then literally propel that

00:23:11.680 --> 00:23:14.680
In a way that it would get into

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:16.680
Wherever they wanted it to get into

00:23:16.680 --> 00:23:19.680
And it would cause disaster and loss of life

00:23:19.680 --> 00:23:21.680
And a fire and perhaps chaos

00:23:21.680 --> 00:23:23.680
More like a little missile

00:23:23.680 --> 00:23:25.680
As we would word it today

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:26.680
Missile launcher

00:23:26.680 --> 00:23:28.680
But obviously of a long time ago

00:23:28.680 --> 00:23:29.680
And what happened is

00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:31.680
He said, there are these manjaniq

00:23:31.680 --> 00:23:32.680
In this home

00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:36.680
Together with so many different armors

00:23:36.680 --> 00:23:37.680
And swords

00:23:37.680 --> 00:23:39.680
And many different weapons

00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:41.680
So it happened that the following day

00:23:41.680 --> 00:23:43.680
They fought, the Muslims overcame them

00:23:43.680 --> 00:23:46.680
They were led to this home

00:23:46.680 --> 00:23:50.680
And before the Muslims actually went in

00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:52.680
There is something historic

00:23:52.680 --> 00:23:53.680
That took place in Khyber

00:23:53.680 --> 00:23:55.680
So much of the seerah

00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:57.680
So much of the ahadeeth

00:23:57.680 --> 00:23:59.680
That make mention of rules and regulations

00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:00.680
You find

00:24:00.680 --> 00:24:01.680
If you were to look

00:24:01.680 --> 00:24:02.680
Where did this come from?

00:24:02.680 --> 00:24:04.680
It was when they were in Khyber

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:07.680
The Muslims spent just under a month in Khyber

00:24:07.680 --> 00:24:08.680
According to some narrations

00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:10.680
Which means a long period of time

00:24:10.680 --> 00:24:11.680
They were in Khyber

00:24:11.680 --> 00:24:13.680
And some of the forts

00:24:13.680 --> 00:24:15.680
They had gone in without a battle

00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:17.680
Some of them they had surrounded them

00:24:17.680 --> 00:24:18.680
For a few days

00:24:18.680 --> 00:24:20.680
Some of them they had fought

00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:21.680
And got in

00:24:21.680 --> 00:24:24.680
So there were different types of entrances

00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:26.680
Into the forts by the Muslimin

00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:27.680
That evening

00:24:27.680 --> 00:24:29.680
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:29.680 --> 00:24:30.680
Looks at his companions

00:24:30.680 --> 00:24:31.680
And he speaks to

00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:33.680
Muhammad ibn Maslamah r.a

00:24:33.680 --> 00:24:34.680
Who was a warrior?

00:24:34.680 --> 00:24:35.680
He was known as one of the leaders

00:24:35.680 --> 00:24:37.680
Of the Muslim armies

00:24:37.680 --> 00:24:38.680
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam says

00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:43.680
Tomorrow I will give this flag

00:24:43.680 --> 00:24:48.680
To a man whom Allah and his messenger love

00:24:48.680 --> 00:24:49.680
And he loves them

00:24:49.680 --> 00:24:52.680
A man who loves Allah and his messenger

00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:54.680
And they love him as well

00:24:54.680 --> 00:24:57.680
So everyone spent the night

00:24:57.680 --> 00:24:59.680
Hoping that it was going to be them

00:24:59.680 --> 00:25:01.680
Umar ibn Al-Khattab r.a

00:25:01.680 --> 00:25:02.680
Who says

00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:04.680
Never ever had I hoped to be given

00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:05.680
Some form of honor

00:25:05.680 --> 00:25:07.680
Than that particular day

00:25:07.680 --> 00:25:10.680
Because Allah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:10.680 --> 00:25:11.680
Is bearing witness

00:25:11.680 --> 00:25:12.680
With the blessed lips

00:25:12.680 --> 00:25:14.680
Of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:16.680
That a man who loves Allah

00:25:16.680 --> 00:25:17.680
And his messenger

00:25:17.680 --> 00:25:19.680
And Allah and his messenger

00:25:19.680 --> 00:25:20.680
Love him too

00:25:21.680 --> 00:25:22.680
In the morning

00:25:22.680 --> 00:25:24.680
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:25.680
Calls out

00:25:25.680 --> 00:25:28.680
Where is Ali ibn Abi Talib r.a

00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:29.680
So they said

00:25:29.680 --> 00:25:30.680
Well he is somewhere

00:25:30.680 --> 00:25:32.680
Because he is complaining of his eye

00:25:32.680 --> 00:25:34.680
He had an infection in his eye

00:25:34.680 --> 00:25:35.680
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:36.680
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:36.680 --> 00:25:37.680
Called him

00:25:37.680 --> 00:25:39.680
And blew into his eye

00:25:39.680 --> 00:25:40.680
With a slight bit of saliva

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:42.680
Going into his eye

00:25:42.680 --> 00:25:45.680
And it was cured almost instantly

00:25:45.680 --> 00:25:46.680
Subhanallah

00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:48.680
This was a miracle of Nubuwa as well

00:25:48.680 --> 00:25:50.680
He blew into the eye

00:25:50.680 --> 00:25:52.680
And Ali r.a was cured

00:25:52.680 --> 00:25:53.680
He gave Ali

00:25:53.680 --> 00:25:56.680
That flag and that title

00:25:56.680 --> 00:25:58.680
And the honor of the day

00:25:58.680 --> 00:26:00.680
And he reminded Ali

00:26:00.680 --> 00:26:01.680
That oh Ali r.a

00:26:01.680 --> 00:26:03.680
You are going into Khaybar

00:26:03.680 --> 00:26:05.680
You are going to enter here

00:26:05.680 --> 00:26:06.680
Remember

00:26:06.680 --> 00:26:10.680
لَأَنْ يَهْدِيَ اللَّهُ بِكَ رَجُلًا وَاحِدًا

00:26:10.680 --> 00:26:13.680
خَيْرٌ لَكَ مِنْ حُمُرِ النَّعْمِ

00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:16.680
For Allah to guide through you

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:19.680
One person is better for you

00:26:19.680 --> 00:26:21.680
Than the most expensive

00:26:21.680 --> 00:26:22.680
Of the material wealth

00:26:22.680 --> 00:26:24.680
That we have here

00:26:24.680 --> 00:26:25.680
It was known as

00:26:25.680 --> 00:26:27.680
Which means the red camel

00:26:27.680 --> 00:26:28.680
