00:36:19.680 --> 00:36:21.680
So later on they found the whole treasure

00:36:21.680 --> 00:36:22.680
The Muslims

00:36:22.680 --> 00:36:25.680
The Prophet s.a.w. instructed that this man

00:36:25.680 --> 00:36:26.680
We don't want to forgive him

00:36:26.680 --> 00:36:28.680
Like we are going to forgive the rest

00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:29.680
See the rest were forgiven

00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:30.680
Why were they forgiven?

00:36:30.680 --> 00:36:32.680
They pleaded with the Prophet s.a.w.

00:36:32.680 --> 00:36:34.680
Please don't execute us

00:36:34.680 --> 00:36:36.680
And please don't send us anywhere and so on

00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:38.680
The Prophet s.a.w. agreed

00:36:38.680 --> 00:36:41.680
It is reported that 93 from amongst them

00:36:41.680 --> 00:36:43.680
Lost their lives on that day

00:36:43.680 --> 00:36:44.680
From amongst the enemy

00:36:44.680 --> 00:36:45.680
And from amongst the Muslims

00:36:45.680 --> 00:36:47.680
15 martyrs

00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:50.680
In the whole stay in Khyber

00:36:50.680 --> 00:36:52.680
15 martyrs and from them 93

00:36:52.680 --> 00:36:54.680
The rest of them were allowed to remain there

00:36:54.680 --> 00:36:56.680
And they were working on the fields

00:36:56.680 --> 00:36:59.680
From amongst those who were taken

00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:00.680
Captive

00:37:00.680 --> 00:37:02.680
Prisoner of war

00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:05.680
One of them was Safiyah binti Huyay

00:37:05.680 --> 00:37:07.680
The daughter of this Huyay ibn Akhtab

00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:09.680
Who was executed in Banu Quraidah

00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:14.220
So when she was taken captive

00:37:14.220 --> 00:37:17.220
The Prophet s.a.w.

00:37:17.220 --> 00:37:21.220
Then married her after she accepted Islam

00:37:21.220 --> 00:37:23.220
Safiyah binti Huyay r.a

00:37:23.220 --> 00:37:25.220
She became known as Ummul Mumineen

00:37:25.220 --> 00:37:27.220
It is reported she became one of the most

00:37:27.220 --> 00:37:30.220
Pious Muslim ladies that there was

00:37:30.220 --> 00:37:31.220
Subhanallah

00:37:31.220 --> 00:37:32.220
And she was such

00:37:32.220 --> 00:37:35.220
She was a soft spoken person

00:37:35.220 --> 00:37:39.220
And she had a lot of respect for the Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:37:39.220 --> 00:37:41.220
Obviously being Ummul Mumineen

00:37:41.220 --> 00:37:43.220
The Prophet s.a.w. married her

00:37:43.220 --> 00:37:46.220
And protected that leadership

00:37:46.220 --> 00:37:48.220
Meaning the high status

00:37:48.220 --> 00:37:50.220
That she had had before

00:37:50.220 --> 00:37:51.220
When she accepted Islam

00:37:51.220 --> 00:37:53.220
She got an even higher status

00:37:53.220 --> 00:37:56.220
Because now she was the wife of Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:37:56.220 --> 00:37:58.220
She used to be the daughter of a leader

00:37:58.220 --> 00:38:01.220
Now she became the wife of a supreme leader

00:38:01.220 --> 00:38:02.220
Subhanallah

00:38:02.220 --> 00:38:05.220
May Allah s.a.w. grant us understanding

00:38:05.220 --> 00:38:07.220
And may He open our doors

00:38:07.220 --> 00:38:09.220
And may He grant us really spouses

00:38:09.220 --> 00:38:12.220
Who will be the coolness of our eyes

00:38:12.220 --> 00:38:13.220
So Alhamdulillah

00:38:13.220 --> 00:38:15.220
This was what happened in Khaybar

00:38:15.220 --> 00:38:17.220
The Prophet s.a.w. was married

00:38:17.220 --> 00:38:20.220
We spoke about his marriage to Ummu Habibah

00:38:20.220 --> 00:38:22.220
Her name was Ramla binti Abi Sufyan

00:38:22.220 --> 00:38:23.220
In Habasha

00:38:23.220 --> 00:38:24.220
We spoke about the reasons

00:38:24.220 --> 00:38:26.220
Here Safiyah binti Khayyai

00:38:26.220 --> 00:38:27.220
We spoke about the reasons

00:38:27.220 --> 00:38:28.220
And at the same time

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:31.220
There was a type of marriage

00:38:31.220 --> 00:38:34.220
That was prevalent from the pagan days

00:38:34.220 --> 00:38:35.220
On the day of Khaybar

00:38:35.220 --> 00:38:37.220
The Prophet s.a.w. got up

00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:38.220
And made an announcement

00:38:38.220 --> 00:38:39.220
That Allah has revealed to me

00:38:39.220 --> 00:38:41.220
That this type of marriage is prohibited

00:38:41.220 --> 00:38:42.220
From this day on

00:38:42.220 --> 00:38:44.220
What was the type of marriage?

00:38:44.220 --> 00:38:45.220
From the pagan days

00:38:45.220 --> 00:38:47.220
They used to marry a woman

00:38:47.220 --> 00:38:49.220
When they were on journey

00:38:49.220 --> 00:38:51.220
Or some way for convenience

00:38:51.220 --> 00:38:52.220
They would marry a woman

00:38:52.220 --> 00:38:54.220
With an expiry date

00:38:54.220 --> 00:38:56.220
On the marriage certificate

00:38:56.220 --> 00:38:57.220
Believe me

00:38:57.220 --> 00:38:59.220
There was actually an expiry date there

00:38:59.220 --> 00:39:00.220
Look at all the smiles here

00:39:00.220 --> 00:39:01.220
Allahu Akbar

00:39:01.220 --> 00:39:03.220
Allah safeguard us

00:39:03.220 --> 00:39:06.220
This was known as Nikah al-Muta'ah

00:39:06.220 --> 00:39:09.220
The Prophet s.a.w. clearly said

00:39:09.220 --> 00:39:11.220
In ahadith that are extremely authentic

00:39:11.220 --> 00:39:13.220
In most books of hadith

00:39:13.220 --> 00:39:14.220
You will find the ahadith

00:39:14.220 --> 00:39:15.220
On the day of Khaybar

00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:17.220
He stood up and he made an announcement

00:39:17.220 --> 00:39:20.220
That this type of marriage is prohibited

00:39:20.220 --> 00:39:21.220
It was a pagan marriage

00:39:21.220 --> 00:39:23.220
That followed through from the time

00:39:23.220 --> 00:39:24.220
And as you know

00:39:24.220 --> 00:39:26.220
Things were being made prohibited in stages

00:39:26.220 --> 00:39:28.220
So on the day of Khaybar

00:39:28.220 --> 00:39:29.220
That was prohibited

00:39:29.220 --> 00:39:31.220
And at the same time

00:39:31.220 --> 00:39:34.220
The consumption of donkeys was also prohibited

00:39:34.220 --> 00:39:36.220
It was permissible before that

00:39:36.220 --> 00:39:37.220
But from that day

00:39:37.220 --> 00:39:40.220
The domesticated donkey prohibited

00:39:40.220 --> 00:39:41.220
Nobody is allowed to eat that anymore

00:39:41.220 --> 00:39:42.220
Subhanallah

00:39:42.220 --> 00:39:45.220
So I see nobody eats donkeys

00:39:45.220 --> 00:39:47.220
May Allah s.a.w. grant us protection

00:39:47.220 --> 00:39:49.220
And may He open our doors

00:39:49.220 --> 00:39:50.220
And as we said

00:39:50.220 --> 00:39:52.220
This Nikah, a temporary marriage

00:39:52.220 --> 00:39:55.220
Was prohibited by the Prophet s.a.w.

00:39:55.220 --> 00:39:57.220
These marriages that are temporary

00:39:57.220 --> 00:39:59.220
Known as Mut'ah

00:39:59.220 --> 00:40:01.220
Where a person gets married for a few hours

00:40:01.220 --> 00:40:03.220
Or a few days or a few months

00:40:03.220 --> 00:40:05.220
Or a convenient time

00:40:05.220 --> 00:40:07.220
And decides I will pay you in year

00:40:07.220 --> 00:40:09.220
Of the amount of time I have stayed with you

00:40:09.220 --> 00:40:11.220
Prohibited on the day of Khaybar

00:40:11.220 --> 00:40:12.220
And we should all know this

00:40:12.220 --> 00:40:15.220
And we should understand and realize this

00:40:15.220 --> 00:40:17.220
As the ghanayim

00:40:17.220 --> 00:40:18.220
Ghanayim

00:40:18.220 --> 00:40:21.220
Ghanayim meaning the spoils of war

00:40:21.220 --> 00:40:22.220
Were now being gathered

00:40:22.220 --> 00:40:25.220
Something very, very powerful happened

00:40:25.220 --> 00:40:29.220
Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:40:29.220 --> 00:40:31.220
He came with the group of people

00:40:31.220 --> 00:40:33.220
Who had migrated to Abyssinia

00:40:33.220 --> 00:40:35.220
He arrived that day in Khaybar

00:40:35.220 --> 00:40:36.220
Subhanallah

00:40:36.220 --> 00:40:39.220
As he was coming back to Al-Madinah al-Munawwara

00:40:39.220 --> 00:40:42.220
Khaybar is not very far out from Madinah al-Munawwara

00:40:42.220 --> 00:40:45.220
Perhaps approximately 100 miles out of Madinah

00:40:45.220 --> 00:40:48.220
So Ja'far ibn Abi Talib came with the

00:40:48.220 --> 00:40:50.220
Rest of the sahabah r.a.

00:40:50.220 --> 00:40:53.220
It's reported that when the Prophet s.a.w. saw him

00:40:53.220 --> 00:40:55.220
He kissed him on his forehead

00:40:55.220 --> 00:40:57.220
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:57.220 --> 00:41:00.220
And thereafter he gave them a good share

00:41:00.220 --> 00:41:04.220
From what was received on the day of Khaybar

00:41:04.220 --> 00:41:06.220
The Muslims became extremely wealthy

00:41:06.220 --> 00:41:07.220
Subhanallah

00:41:07.220 --> 00:41:10.220
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had sent down

00:41:10.220 --> 00:41:12.220
So many rules and regulations

00:41:12.220 --> 00:41:15.220
Regarding what was received on the day of Khaybar

00:41:15.220 --> 00:41:18.220
And it was given also to Ja'far ibn Abi Talib

00:41:18.220 --> 00:41:19.220
And those who were very poor people

00:41:19.220 --> 00:41:21.220
Who had gone to Habasha

00:41:21.220 --> 00:41:23.220
Also something very interesting

00:41:23.220 --> 00:41:25.220
Abu Musa al-Ash'ari

00:41:25.220 --> 00:41:28.220
From the Ash'ari tribe

00:41:28.220 --> 00:41:31.220
They had left Yemen

00:41:31.220 --> 00:41:33.220
In order to get to Muhammad s.a.w.

00:41:33.220 --> 00:41:34.220
They jumped into the boat

00:41:34.220 --> 00:41:36.220
And they say their boat drifted

00:41:36.220 --> 00:41:37.220
And it ended in Habasha

00:41:37.220 --> 00:41:39.220
It ended in Abyssinia

00:41:39.220 --> 00:41:41.220
They met Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:41:41.220 --> 00:41:44.220
Remained there with him until the day he left

00:41:44.220 --> 00:41:46.220
So they also arrived in Khaybar

00:41:46.220 --> 00:41:48.220
Together with Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:41:48.220 --> 00:41:50.220
Abu Musa al-Ash'ari r.a.

00:41:50.220 --> 00:41:52.220
He has narrated so many hadiths

00:41:52.220 --> 00:41:54.220
Of the Prophet s.a.w.

00:41:54.220 --> 00:41:56.220
He says I was the youngest of the lot on that day

00:41:56.220 --> 00:41:57.220
Alhamdulillah

00:41:57.220 --> 00:42:00.220
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:42:00.220 --> 00:42:02.220
This was what had happened at that particular time

00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:06.220
Then after the battle of Khaybar

00:42:06.220 --> 00:42:09.220
There were several groups of people

00:42:09.220 --> 00:42:12.220
Who were also from amongst the people

00:42:12.220 --> 00:42:14.220
Similar to those in Khaybar

00:42:14.220 --> 00:42:17.220
Who had had settled in various places

00:42:17.220 --> 00:42:19.220
The Muslim army went

00:42:19.220 --> 00:42:21.220
And what they did is

00:42:21.220 --> 00:42:25.220
One by one they struck agreements with them

00:42:25.220 --> 00:42:27.220
They made peace with them in some places

00:42:27.220 --> 00:42:29.220
There was a little bit of a skirmish

00:42:29.220 --> 00:42:30.220
A bit of a war

00:42:30.220 --> 00:42:32.220
And thereafter there was an agreement signed

00:42:32.220 --> 00:42:34.220
And the Prophet s.a.w.

00:42:34.220 --> 00:42:36.220
Either removed them or

00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:38.220
He kept them in some instances

00:42:38.220 --> 00:42:40.220
And told them you may plant

00:42:40.220 --> 00:42:41.220
And you may harvest

00:42:41.220 --> 00:42:43.220
And we will share half half

00:42:43.220 --> 00:42:46.220
Just as we did with the people of Khaybar

00:42:46.220 --> 00:42:48.220
So from amongst these were

00:42:48.220 --> 00:42:50.220
Those of Wadi Al-Qura

00:42:50.220 --> 00:42:51.220
Wadi Al-Qura was an area

00:42:51.220 --> 00:42:54.220
Where the Muslims also became victorious thereafter

00:42:54.220 --> 00:42:58.220
Fadak was also given to Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:42:58.220 --> 00:43:00.220
By Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:43:00.220 --> 00:43:02.220
For himself and his family

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:05.220
Which means whatever came from Fadak

00:43:05.220 --> 00:43:07.220
It was meant for the clan of the Prophet s.a.w.

00:43:07.220 --> 00:43:09.220
The poor from amongst them

00:43:09.220 --> 00:43:10.220
Were looked after by it

00:43:10.220 --> 00:43:12.220
More like an endowment

00:43:12.220 --> 00:43:15.220
To look after those from there

00:43:15.220 --> 00:43:18.220
Then after in fact there was another area

00:43:18.220 --> 00:43:19.220
Also known as Tayma

00:43:19.220 --> 00:43:22.220
Where also the Muslims had become victorious

00:43:22.220 --> 00:43:24.220
After Wadi Al-Qura

00:43:24.220 --> 00:43:27.220
Something very powerful happened

00:43:27.220 --> 00:43:29.220
The Prophet s.a.w.

00:43:29.220 --> 00:43:32.220
If you recall the previous year

00:43:32.220 --> 00:43:35.220
They had been stopped from going

00:43:35.220 --> 00:43:36.220
To fulfill the Umrah

00:43:36.220 --> 00:43:39.220
Now a year later they were planning

00:43:39.220 --> 00:43:40.220
To go for that Umrah

00:43:40.220 --> 00:43:41.220
According to the agreement

00:43:41.220 --> 00:43:43.220
Quraish said we will come out of the Haram

00:43:43.220 --> 00:43:45.220
For three days you will come in

00:43:45.220 --> 00:43:47.220
So the Prophet s.a.w.

00:43:47.220 --> 00:43:49.220
Got his companions ready

00:43:49.220 --> 00:43:50.220
According to one narration

00:43:50.220 --> 00:43:53.220
He wore his Ahraam from the Masjid al-Nabawi

00:43:53.220 --> 00:43:56.220
And as they went out by Dhul-Hulaifa

00:43:56.220 --> 00:43:58.220
He instructed his companions

00:43:58.220 --> 00:43:59.220
To take their weapons

00:43:59.220 --> 00:44:02.220
They said oh messenger s.a.w.

00:44:02.220 --> 00:44:05.220
We promised these people not to take our weapons

00:44:05.220 --> 00:44:08.220
He said no we will not take them into the Haram

00:44:08.220 --> 00:44:11.220
But in case someone intends to break

00:44:11.220 --> 00:44:13.220
Any agreement we will be ready

00:44:13.220 --> 00:44:15.220
This time we are going to have it

00:44:15.220 --> 00:44:16.220
So they took their weapons

00:44:16.220 --> 00:44:18.220
And they proceeded from the Dhul-Hulaifa

00:44:18.220 --> 00:44:20.220
Until one of the

00:44:20.220 --> 00:44:23.220
In fact the Mushriks had sent out a little army

00:44:23.220 --> 00:44:25.220
When they got to the Muslims

00:44:25.220 --> 00:44:27.220
They saw these people are heavily armed

00:44:27.220 --> 00:44:29.220
They went back to report to Quraish

00:44:29.220 --> 00:44:31.220
And Abu Sufyan and the others

00:44:31.220 --> 00:44:32.220
That the Muslims are coming

00:44:32.220 --> 00:44:33.220
But they are heavily armed

00:44:33.220 --> 00:44:35.220
Immediately they sent messengers to say

00:44:35.220 --> 00:44:38.220
Oh Muhammad s.a.w.

00:44:38.220 --> 00:44:40.220
We never ever knew you

00:44:40.220 --> 00:44:43.220
To break a single promise in your life

00:44:43.220 --> 00:44:46.220
Why is it that you are coming with weapons

00:44:46.220 --> 00:44:48.220
He said according to our agreement

00:44:48.220 --> 00:44:50.220
We will not enter Makkah with weapons

00:44:50.220 --> 00:44:52.220
So we will leave our weapons outside Makkah

00:44:52.220 --> 00:44:53.220
And then we will enter

00:44:53.220 --> 00:44:55.220
Subhanallah

00:44:55.220 --> 00:44:57.220
So the Prophet s.a.w.

00:44:57.220 --> 00:44:58.220
Was extremely intelligent

00:44:58.220 --> 00:45:01.220
It is reported in some of the books of history

00:45:01.220 --> 00:45:03.220
That had they not taken these weapons

00:45:03.220 --> 00:45:06.220
Perhaps these people with their evil intentions

00:45:06.220 --> 00:45:08.220
May have wanted to wipe out the Muslims

00:45:08.220 --> 00:45:09.220
Only Allah knows

00:45:09.220 --> 00:45:12.220
May Allah s.a.w. grant us strength

00:45:12.220 --> 00:45:14.220
So the Prophet s.a.w.

00:45:14.220 --> 00:45:16.220
Had had 70 camels

00:45:16.220 --> 00:45:18.220
Sorry 60 camels for Hadi

00:45:18.220 --> 00:45:20.220
Hadi meaning sacrificial animals

00:45:20.220 --> 00:45:23.220
Which they wanted to sacrifice in Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:45:23.220 --> 00:45:25.220
And when they got to a place

00:45:25.220 --> 00:45:27.220
Known as Thaniyat Kada

00:45:27.220 --> 00:45:29.220
They left some of the companions there

00:45:29.220 --> 00:45:31.220
And they left their weapons there

00:45:31.220 --> 00:45:33.220
And they proceeded into the Haram

00:45:33.220 --> 00:45:36.220
Whilst Quraysh had just left the Haram

00:45:36.220 --> 00:45:39.220
Haram meaning it is not such a big area

00:45:39.220 --> 00:45:42.220
The Quraysh in fact the leaders had left

00:45:42.220 --> 00:45:45.220
Some of the smaller people

00:45:45.220 --> 00:45:47.220
Who were not so important in Quraysh

00:45:47.220 --> 00:45:49.220
Were there

00:45:49.220 --> 00:45:50.220
However what had happened is

00:45:50.220 --> 00:45:52.220
They were sitting on a hillock

00:45:52.220 --> 00:45:53.220
And they began to say

00:45:53.220 --> 00:45:55.220
You see these people in a Haram

00:45:55.220 --> 00:45:56.220
This is important we listen to this

00:45:56.220 --> 00:45:58.220
Because it affects us when we go for Umrah

00:45:58.220 --> 00:46:00.220
Now

00:46:00.220 --> 00:46:02.220
The people of Quraysh began to say

00:46:02.220 --> 00:46:03.220
You see these people in a Haram

00:46:03.220 --> 00:46:04.220
They are sick

00:46:04.220 --> 00:46:06.220
They have the disease of Yathrib

00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:07.220
If you recall we said

00:46:07.220 --> 00:46:09.220
In Madinah there was a disease

00:46:09.220 --> 00:46:12.220
There was a plague or a flu

00:46:12.220 --> 00:46:13.220
Or some form of a disease

00:46:13.220 --> 00:46:16.220
That used to overtake them on an annual basis

00:46:16.220 --> 00:46:18.220
And the Prophet s.a.w. made a dua

00:46:18.220 --> 00:46:21.220
And this was actually taken out to Juhfah

00:46:21.220 --> 00:46:23.220
So Quraysh was laughing

00:46:23.220 --> 00:46:24.220
Look at these people

00:46:24.220 --> 00:46:25.220
They are so thin

00:46:25.220 --> 00:46:26.220
They are so small

00:46:26.220 --> 00:46:28.220
We can wipe these people out

00:46:28.220 --> 00:46:30.220
And you know they were just talking and laughing

00:46:30.220 --> 00:46:31.220
Making a joke

00:46:31.220 --> 00:46:33.220
The Prophet s.a.w. then ordered

00:46:33.220 --> 00:46:35.220
What was known as Al-Yutibaa

00:46:35.220 --> 00:46:37.220
And what is known as Ramal

00:46:37.220 --> 00:46:40.220
So he instructed his companions to open

00:46:40.220 --> 00:46:43.220
The right side of the Ahram

00:46:43.220 --> 00:46:44.220
So that the arm is showing

00:46:44.220 --> 00:46:46.220
To show the muscle on the right side

00:46:46.220 --> 00:46:47.220
And stick the chest out

00:46:47.220 --> 00:46:49.220
To show them that we are not little

00:46:49.220 --> 00:46:51.220
You know people who are weaklings

00:46:51.220 --> 00:46:53.220
We are strong men

00:46:53.220 --> 00:46:54.220
And we walk in a proper way

00:46:54.220 --> 00:46:56.220
As though an army is walking

00:46:56.220 --> 00:46:57.220
Subhanallah

00:46:57.220 --> 00:46:58.220
You see when an army is walking

00:46:58.220 --> 00:46:59.220
The way they walk

00:46:59.220 --> 00:47:01.220
They walk with proper posture

00:47:01.220 --> 00:47:03.220
They don't walk slouched and so on

00:47:03.220 --> 00:47:05.220
So as they were walking

00:47:05.220 --> 00:47:06.220
In that particular way

00:47:06.220 --> 00:47:08.220
The Prophet s.a.w. was on his camel

00:47:08.220 --> 00:47:10.220
He made tawaf on his camel

00:47:10.220 --> 00:47:12.220
And when he kissed the hajar

00:47:12.220 --> 00:47:13.220
He did so with his stick

00:47:13.220 --> 00:47:15.220
So he would touch the hajar with his stick

00:47:15.220 --> 00:47:17.220
And then kiss the end of the stick

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:19.220
Which touched the hajar

00:47:19.220 --> 00:47:21.220
This is how the Prophet s.a.w.

00:47:21.220 --> 00:47:23.220
Made that particular tawaf

00:47:23.220 --> 00:47:25.220
On that day of Umratul Qadha

00:47:25.220 --> 00:47:27.220
It is known as Umratul Qadha

00:47:27.220 --> 00:47:29.220
Because it is the Umrah

00:47:29.220 --> 00:47:31.220
That took place as a result

00:47:31.220 --> 00:47:34.220
Of being sent back one of the years

00:47:34.220 --> 00:47:35.220
And coming back again

00:47:35.220 --> 00:47:36.220
So basically they wanted to do it

00:47:36.220 --> 00:47:37.220
The previous year

00:47:37.220 --> 00:47:39.220
They were now recompensing it

00:47:39.220 --> 00:47:41.220
By doing it the following year

00:47:41.220 --> 00:47:43.220
So after three rounds

00:47:43.220 --> 00:47:44.220
These mushriks ran away

00:47:44.220 --> 00:47:46.220
So now they were instructed

00:47:46.220 --> 00:47:49.220
Leave this open for the seven rounds

00:47:49.220 --> 00:47:51.220
But you may now take it a bit calm

00:47:51.220 --> 00:47:52.220
When you are walking

00:47:52.220 --> 00:47:54.220
And for that reason up to today

00:47:54.220 --> 00:47:56.220
When we as men go to Makkah for Umrah

00:47:56.220 --> 00:47:58.220
We need to open the right arm

00:47:58.220 --> 00:48:00.220
For the entire tawaf

00:48:00.220 --> 00:48:02.220
All seven rounds

00:48:02.220 --> 00:48:04.220
And we need to walk briskly

00:48:04.220 --> 00:48:06.220
With our chests sticking out slightly

00:48:06.220 --> 00:48:07.220
For the first three rounds

00:48:07.220 --> 00:48:08.220
I'm sure we know this

00:48:08.220 --> 00:48:10.220
This is the history of it

00:48:10.220 --> 00:48:12.220
May Allah s.a.w. open our doors

00:48:12.220 --> 00:48:13.220
And grant us goodness

00:48:13.220 --> 00:48:17.220
The Prophet s.a.w. thereafter

00:48:17.220 --> 00:48:20.220
When he had completed his Umrah

00:48:20.220 --> 00:48:24.220
There was something that had happened in Makkah

00:48:24.220 --> 00:48:26.220
A lady by the name of

00:48:26.220 --> 00:48:28.220
Maymunatha bint Al-Harith

00:48:28.220 --> 00:48:30.220
R.a.a. al-Hilaliyah

00:48:30.220 --> 00:48:32.220
She was related to Umm al-Fadl

00:48:32.220 --> 00:48:34.220
Being a sister and related to

00:48:34.220 --> 00:48:36.220
Al-Abbas ibn Abdul-Muttalib

00:48:36.220 --> 00:48:38.220
She was from amongst the Muslims

00:48:38.220 --> 00:48:39.220
The early Muslims

00:48:39.220 --> 00:48:41.220
Her husband had passed away as well

00:48:41.220 --> 00:48:44.220
His name was Abu Rahm ibn Abdul-Uzza

00:48:44.220 --> 00:48:47.220
And Al-Abbas r.a.a.

00:48:47.220 --> 00:48:49.220
Wanted to get her married

00:48:49.220 --> 00:48:51.220
To Muhammad s.a.w.

00:48:51.220 --> 00:48:54.220
And she would then go with them

00:48:54.220 --> 00:48:55.220
To Madina Munawwara

00:48:55.220 --> 00:48:57.220
And at least be protected

00:48:57.220 --> 00:48:58.220
So the Prophet s.a.w. agreed

00:48:58.220 --> 00:48:59.220
Masha'Allah

00:48:59.220 --> 00:49:01.220
And this was the last of the women

00:49:01.220 --> 00:49:02.220
That he had married

00:49:02.220 --> 00:49:05.220
Her name was Maymunatha bint Al-Harith

00:49:05.220 --> 00:49:07.220
Al-Hilaliyah r.a.a

00:49:07.220 --> 00:49:10.220
Not related to Juwayriya bint Al-Harith

00:49:10.220 --> 00:49:11.220
Ibn Abi Al-Dhira

00:49:11.220 --> 00:49:13.220
Who was someone else altogether

00:49:13.220 --> 00:49:14.220
We spoke about her

00:49:14.220 --> 00:49:16.220
But they were both co-wives

00:49:16.220 --> 00:49:18.220
Of Muhammad s.a.w.

00:49:18.220 --> 00:49:21.220
So he married her sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:21.220 --> 00:49:26.220
And he took her out with him

00:49:26.220 --> 00:49:29.220
And only later on in Saraf

00:49:29.220 --> 00:49:31.220
Saraf is an area just outside

00:49:31.220 --> 00:49:32.220
Makkatul Mukarrama

00:49:32.220 --> 00:49:33.220
Because they were only allowed

00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:34.220
Three days in Makkah

00:49:34.220 --> 00:49:36.220
After that they had to leave

00:49:36.220 --> 00:49:37.220
The Prophet s.a.w.

00:49:37.220 --> 00:49:38.220
Went to where the weapons were

00:49:38.220 --> 00:49:40.220
And instructed those companions

00:49:40.220 --> 00:49:42.220
To go and make their Umrah

00:49:42.220 --> 00:49:43.220
When they came back

00:49:43.220 --> 00:49:44.220
The Muslim army then left

00:49:44.220 --> 00:49:46.220
The group of Muslims

00:49:46.220 --> 00:49:47.220
When they got to an area

00:49:47.220 --> 00:49:48.220
Known as Saraf

00:49:48.220 --> 00:49:50.220
This is when they had the Walima

00:49:50.220 --> 00:49:53.220
And this is when the Prophet s.a.w.

00:49:53.220 --> 00:49:54.220
Consummated the marriage

00:49:54.220 --> 00:49:56.220
With Maymunatha bint Al-Harith

00:49:56.220 --> 00:49:57.220
R.a.a

00:49:57.220 --> 00:49:59.220
And this was a gift

00:49:59.220 --> 00:50:01.220
That Allah s.w.t. had granted

00:50:01.220 --> 00:50:03.220
Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:50:03.220 --> 00:50:05.220
If we take a look at this

00:50:05.220 --> 00:50:06.220
We will come to know

00:50:06.220 --> 00:50:08.220
That the Prophet s.a.w.

00:50:08.220 --> 00:50:10.220
Was the most noble of all men

00:50:10.220 --> 00:50:11.220
That existed

00:50:11.220 --> 00:50:13.220
He looked after so many people

00:50:13.220 --> 00:50:16.220
And he was related to so many people

00:50:16.220 --> 00:50:17.220
And at the same time

00:50:17.220 --> 00:50:18.220
Subhanallah

00:50:18.220 --> 00:50:20.220
He was of the highest

00:50:20.220 --> 00:50:22.220
Character and conduct ever

00:50:22.220 --> 00:50:23.220
The highest level of character

00:50:23.220 --> 00:50:24.220
The Quran says

00:50:24.220 --> 00:50:30.220
Wa innaka la ala khuluqin azeem

00:50:30.220 --> 00:50:32.220
Indeed you are on the highest level

00:50:32.220 --> 00:50:33.220
Of character and conduct

00:50:33.220 --> 00:50:34.220
Subhanallah

00:50:34.220 --> 00:50:36.220
Before I close this evening

00:50:36.220 --> 00:50:38.220
I want to make mention of

00:50:38.220 --> 00:50:40.220
One of the gifts also

00:50:40.220 --> 00:50:41.220
To the Muslim Ummah

00:50:41.220 --> 00:50:43.220
That had been given

00:50:43.220 --> 00:50:44.220
At that particular time

00:50:44.220 --> 00:50:45.220
After Umrah al-Qadha

00:50:45.220 --> 00:50:47.220
Khalid b.w.

00:50:47.220 --> 00:50:48.220
R.a.a

00:50:48.220 --> 00:50:49.220
Says

00:50:49.220 --> 00:50:51.220
When the messenger came

00:50:51.220 --> 00:50:53.220
When the messenger s.a.w.

00:50:53.220 --> 00:50:55.220
Came for Umrah al-Qadha

00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:57.220
I was a very shy person

00:50:57.220 --> 00:50:59.220
I decided I'm going to go out

00:50:59.220 --> 00:51:01.220
As well with the leaders of Quraysh

00:51:01.220 --> 00:51:02.220
And I disappeared

00:51:02.220 --> 00:51:03.220
I actually disappeared

00:51:03.220 --> 00:51:05.220
I did not want to see the Muslims

00:51:05.220 --> 00:51:06.220
And I did not want to face

00:51:06.220 --> 00:51:07.220
Those whom I had fought

00:51:07.220 --> 00:51:08.220
But

00:51:08.220 --> 00:51:10.220
He says in my heart

00:51:10.220 --> 00:51:11.220
I always knew

00:51:11.220 --> 00:51:12.220
That I'm fighting

00:51:12.220 --> 00:51:14.220
The losing party

00:51:14.220 --> 00:51:15.220
In the losing party

00:51:15.220 --> 00:51:17.220
I'm fighting in the losing party

00:51:17.220 --> 00:51:19.220
Against those who are ultimately

00:51:19.220 --> 00:51:21.220
Going to be victorious

00:51:21.220 --> 00:51:22.220
He always knew it

00:51:22.220 --> 00:51:23.220
He says

00:51:23.220 --> 00:51:24.220
Whether it was in Uhud

00:51:24.220 --> 00:51:25.220
Whether it was in Khandaq

00:51:25.220 --> 00:51:27.220
Whether it was anywhere else

00:51:27.220 --> 00:51:28.220
I always knew

00:51:28.220 --> 00:51:29.220
That I'm not going to win

00:51:29.220 --> 00:51:30.220
Even the platoon

00:51:30.220 --> 00:51:32.220
That he was sent in

00:51:32.220 --> 00:51:33.220
In order to weigh

00:51:33.220 --> 00:51:35.220
Lay the messenger s.a.w.

00:51:35.220 --> 00:51:36.220
When they were coming

00:51:36.220 --> 00:51:38.220
For the Umrah

00:51:38.220 --> 00:51:40.220
And they had then ended up

00:51:40.220 --> 00:51:41.220
In Hudaibiyah

00:51:41.220 --> 00:51:42.220
If you remember

00:51:42.220 --> 00:51:43.220
They changed their path

00:51:43.220 --> 00:51:44.220
Even then he says

00:51:44.220 --> 00:51:45.220
You know what

00:51:45.220 --> 00:51:46.220
This man

00:51:46.220 --> 00:51:47.220
Subhanallah

00:51:47.220 --> 00:51:48.220
He's somehow protected

00:51:48.220 --> 00:51:50.220
So he had had this in his heart

00:51:50.220 --> 00:51:51.220
And he was never very happy

00:51:51.220 --> 00:51:52.220
He always felt

00:51:52.220 --> 00:51:53.220
I'm doing something wrong

00:51:53.220 --> 00:51:54.220
It is reported that

00:51:54.220 --> 00:51:55.220
Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:51:55.220 --> 00:51:57.220
Used to constantly ask

00:51:57.220 --> 00:51:58.220
His brother

00:51:58.220 --> 00:51:59.220
Al-Walid ibn Al-Walid

00:51:59.220 --> 00:52:00.220
Who was a Muslim

00:52:00.220 --> 00:52:01.220
And he was in

00:52:01.220 --> 00:52:02.220
Madina Munawarah

00:52:02.220 --> 00:52:03.220
He used to say

00:52:03.220 --> 00:52:04.220
Where is Khalid?

00:52:04.220 --> 00:52:08.220
A man like Khalid

00:52:08.220 --> 00:52:09.220
So intelligent

00:52:09.220 --> 00:52:10.220
He cannot be ignorant

00:52:10.220 --> 00:52:11.220
Of the fact that

00:52:11.220 --> 00:52:12.220
Islam is the correct religion

00:52:12.220 --> 00:52:14.220
He's so intelligent

00:52:14.220 --> 00:52:15.220
He cannot keep on

00:52:15.220 --> 00:52:16.220
Worshipping his idols

00:52:16.220 --> 00:52:17.220
And so on

00:52:17.220 --> 00:52:18.220
And the Prophet s.a.w.

00:52:18.220 --> 00:52:19.220
Continued to say

00:52:19.220 --> 00:52:20.220
Ya ati bihi Allah

00:52:20.220 --> 00:52:22.220
Allah will bring him soon

00:52:22.220 --> 00:52:24.220
Khalid ibn Al-Walid says

00:52:24.220 --> 00:52:25.220
That you know

00:52:25.220 --> 00:52:26.220
He had some friends

00:52:26.220 --> 00:52:27.220
He spoke to them and so on

00:52:27.220 --> 00:52:28.220
Some gave him this response

00:52:28.220 --> 00:52:29.220
That response

00:52:29.220 --> 00:52:30.220
And he says

00:52:30.220 --> 00:52:31.220
Thereafter

00:52:31.220 --> 00:52:33.220
Amr ibn Al-As

00:52:33.220 --> 00:52:35.220
And Uthman ibn Talha

00:52:35.220 --> 00:52:36.220
The three of them decided

00:52:36.220 --> 00:52:38.220
We're going to Madina Munawarah

00:52:38.220 --> 00:52:40.220
And we're going to accept Islam

00:52:40.220 --> 00:52:41.220
And this was just after

00:52:41.220 --> 00:52:42.220
Umrat Al-Qadha

00:52:42.220 --> 00:52:46.220
But what actually triggered it

00:52:46.220 --> 00:52:47.220
Was something powerful

00:52:47.220 --> 00:52:49.220
A letter written by

00:52:49.220 --> 00:52:50.220
Al-Walid ibn Al-Walid

00:52:50.220 --> 00:52:51.220
Who is the brother of

00:52:51.220 --> 00:52:52.220
Khalid ibn Al-Walid

00:52:52.220 --> 00:52:54.220
To his own brother Khalid

00:52:54.220 --> 00:52:56.220
When he went for Umrat Al-Qadha

00:52:56.220 --> 00:52:57.220
He went to search for his brother

00:52:57.220 --> 00:52:58.220
He wanted to tell him

00:52:58.220 --> 00:52:59.220
My brother come on

00:52:59.220 --> 00:53:00.220
You cannot continue

00:53:00.220 --> 00:53:01.220
On the wrong side

00:53:01.220 --> 00:53:03.220
You've missed a lot of goodness

00:53:03.220 --> 00:53:04.220
But because he didn't

00:53:04.220 --> 00:53:05.220
Meet his brother

00:53:05.220 --> 00:53:06.220
He wrote a letter and left it there

00:53:06.220 --> 00:53:07.220
The brother came back

00:53:07.220 --> 00:53:09.220
Read the letter from his brother

00:53:09.220 --> 00:53:10.220
He's saying you know what

00:53:10.220 --> 00:53:11.220
Oh Khalid

00:53:11.220 --> 00:53:12.220
You are on the wrong camp

00:53:12.220 --> 00:53:13.220
You are in the wrong side

00:53:13.220 --> 00:53:14.220
In the wrong camp

00:53:14.220 --> 00:53:15.220
On the wrong side

00:53:15.220 --> 00:53:16.220
And at the same time

00:53:16.220 --> 00:53:17.220
Oh Khalid

00:53:17.220 --> 00:53:18.220
You are missing so much goodness

00:53:18.220 --> 00:53:20.220
We are living in such goodness

00:53:20.220 --> 00:53:22.220
We have highest character

00:53:22.220 --> 00:53:23.220
Conduct

00:53:23.220 --> 00:53:25.220
We are worshipping Allah alone

00:53:25.220 --> 00:53:27.220
We have left all the evil of the past

00:53:27.220 --> 00:53:28.220
And so on

00:53:28.220 --> 00:53:29.220
Subhanallah

00:53:29.220 --> 00:53:31.220
Khalid ibn Al-Walid

00:53:31.220 --> 00:53:32.220
It was written in the letter

00:53:32.220 --> 00:53:33.220
That the messenger

00:53:33.220 --> 00:53:34.220
Keeps asking about you

00:53:34.220 --> 00:53:35.220
And he has hope

00:53:35.220 --> 00:53:36.220
That you are definitely

00:53:36.220 --> 00:53:37.220
Going to come

00:53:37.220 --> 00:53:38.220
And he has told us

00:53:38.220 --> 00:53:39.220
That you are going to come

00:53:40.220 --> 00:53:41.220
So Khalid ibn Al-Walid

00:53:41.220 --> 00:53:42.220
Closed that letter

00:53:42.220 --> 00:53:43.220
He asked a few people

00:53:43.220 --> 00:53:44.220
Some questions

00:53:44.220 --> 00:53:45.220
He got hold of two of his friends

00:53:45.220 --> 00:53:46.220
Amr ibn Al-Asr radiallahu anhu

00:53:46.220 --> 00:53:47.220
As well as

00:53:48.220 --> 00:53:50.220
Uthman ibn Talha radiallahu anhu

00:53:50.220 --> 00:53:51.220
The three of them went to

00:53:51.220 --> 00:53:52.220
Madina Munawwara

00:53:52.220 --> 00:53:53.220
And I'm cutting the story

00:53:53.220 --> 00:53:54.220
A little bit short

00:53:54.220 --> 00:53:55.220
When they got to

00:53:55.220 --> 00:53:56.220
Madina Munawwara

00:53:56.220 --> 00:53:57.220
They went

00:53:58.220 --> 00:53:59.220
And his brother told him

00:53:59.220 --> 00:54:00.220
Make haste

00:54:00.220 --> 00:54:01.220
Go to Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:54:01.220 --> 00:54:02.220
He knows you are coming

00:54:02.220 --> 00:54:03.220
And he's waiting for you

00:54:03.220 --> 00:54:05.220
So he wore some good clothing

00:54:05.220 --> 00:54:06.220
He had a bath and so on

00:54:06.220 --> 00:54:07.220
And they rushed to

00:54:07.220 --> 00:54:08.220
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:54:14.220 --> 00:54:15.220
Subhanallah

00:54:15.220 --> 00:54:16.220
What happened?

00:54:17.220 --> 00:54:19.220
One of the great warriors

00:54:19.220 --> 00:54:22.220
One of those who was fighting

00:54:22.220 --> 00:54:24.220
Against Islam

00:54:24.220 --> 00:54:26.220
Has now turned to Islam

00:54:26.220 --> 00:54:27.220
Khalid ibn Al-Walid

00:54:27.220 --> 00:54:30.220
The man who was guilty

00:54:30.220 --> 00:54:32.220
Of slaughtering so many Muslims

00:54:32.220 --> 00:54:34.220
On the day of Uhud

00:54:34.220 --> 00:54:35.220
Here he is

00:54:35.220 --> 00:54:36.220
He came to Madina

00:54:36.220 --> 00:54:37.220
Safe and sound

00:54:37.220 --> 00:54:38.220
He says

00:54:38.220 --> 00:54:39.220
Oh messenger

00:54:39.220 --> 00:54:40.220
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:54:40.220 --> 00:54:41.220
These are his first words

00:54:41.220 --> 00:54:42.220
He says

00:54:42.220 --> 00:54:43.220
Make dua

00:54:43.220 --> 00:54:44.220
That Allah forgive me

00:54:44.220 --> 00:54:45.220
For every time

00:54:45.220 --> 00:54:46.220
I have been used

00:54:46.220 --> 00:54:48.220
In order to attack

00:54:48.220 --> 00:54:50.220
Yourself and the Muslims

00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:51.220
And all the harm

00:54:51.220 --> 00:54:52.220
That I have caused

00:54:52.220 --> 00:54:53.220
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:54:53.220 --> 00:54:54.220
Says

00:54:54.220 --> 00:54:55.220
Ya Khalid

00:54:56.220 --> 00:54:57.220
Oh Khalid

00:54:57.220 --> 00:54:58.220
Islam deletes

00:54:58.220 --> 00:54:59.220
All the bad

00:54:59.220 --> 00:55:00.220
That was done before it

00:55:00.220 --> 00:55:01.220
The minute you accept Islam

00:55:01.220 --> 00:55:02.220
Everything wiped out

00:55:02.220 --> 00:55:03.220
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:55:03.220 --> 00:55:04.220
Had a smile

00:55:04.220 --> 00:55:05.220
Then

00:55:05.220 --> 00:55:06.220
In some narration

00:55:06.220 --> 00:55:08.220
Say he repeated this thrice

00:55:08.220 --> 00:55:09.220
And Khalid

00:55:09.220 --> 00:55:10.220
Radhiallahu anhu

00:55:10.220 --> 00:55:11.220
Says

00:55:11.220 --> 00:55:12.220
Ala thalik

00:55:12.220 --> 00:55:13.220
Upon that condition

00:55:13.220 --> 00:55:14.220
Which means

00:55:14.220 --> 00:55:15.220
If it is that

00:55:15.220 --> 00:55:16.220
Alhamdulillah

00:55:16.220 --> 00:55:17.220
We thank Allah

00:55:17.220 --> 00:55:18.220
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:55:18.220 --> 00:55:19.220
He forgives us

